medical_history.chief_complaint: Abdominal pain with associated nausea and vomiting.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The symptoms began at 3 AM this morning, waking the patient from sleep. The patient was in normal health until the previous night after a drive home. After falling asleep for 45 minutes, he developed severe dull, nonradiating abdominal pain around the umbilicus. There has been a decreased appetite since the onset of symptoms. The patient presented to the ED due to continued abdominal pain.
medical_history.family_history: No family history of inflammatory bowel disease.
